    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="344"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./294:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 28, 1929—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Department advised by All American Cables that MacGregor, who has just
                    reached Panama from Tegucigalpa, reports considerable opposition to ratification
                    of aviation contract. You will please report situation fully. As this company is
                    under contract with United States Government for carrying of mails to Panama
                    Canal, this Government is anxious that it obtain the necessary permission in the
                    countries through which the company has to pass.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
